<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:282px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Alive-andes-6.jpg" class="image" title="The Old Christians rugby team, Stella Maris College, Montevideo; Fernando Parrado is the seventh person standing up from the right."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/Alive-andes-6.jpg/280px-Alive-andes-6.jpg" width="280" height="184" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Alive-andes-6.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
The <i>Old Christians</i> rugby team, <i>Stella Maris</i> College, Montevideo; Fernando Parrado is the seventh person standing up from the right.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Uruguayan Air Force Flight 571</b>, also known less formally as the <b>Andes flight disaster</b>, was an airline flight carrying 45 people that <a href="/wiki/Accidents_and_incidents_in_aviation" title="Accidents and incidents in aviation" class="mw-redirect">crashed</a> in the <a href="/wiki/Andes" title="Andes">Andes</a> on October 13, 1972. The event was concluded by December 23, 1972, when the last of 16 survivors were rescued. More than a quarter of the passengers died in the crash and several survivors of the initial impact had died of cold and injuries by the next day.</p>
<p>The remaining survivors had very little food and no way to make heat in the harsh climate, over 10,000 feet <a href="/wiki/Altitude" title="Altitude">altitude</a>. Faced with starvation the survivors eventually fed on the dead passengers who were preserved in the snow. Rescue teams were not aware of the survivors until 72 days after the crash when <a href="/wiki/Nando_Parrado" title="Nando Parrado">Nando Parrado</a> and <a href="/wiki/Roberto_Canessa" title="Roberto Canessa">Roberto Canessa</a>, after a 12 day trek across the treacherous Andes mountains, found a <a href="/wiki/Chile" title="Chile">Chilean</a> <a href="/wiki/Huaso" title="Huaso">huaso</a> who guided them to safety where help was found for the other survivors still trapped at the crash site.</p>
